data.title: Oran Etkin & Kelenia at Israeli JazzPhest , November 10
data.meta_description: Oran Etkin & Kelenia at Israeli JazzPhest , November 10. Musicians: Oran Etkin & Kelenia, Mattan Klein, Omer Avital, Shai Maestro,  - order tickets, find location and other info. Never miss another jazz concert in Philadelphia again!
data.text:
Israeli JazzPhest (Nov. 10-20) kicks off with Oran Etkin and Kelenia at the Philadelphia Clef Club of Jazz. Grammy nominated clarinetist, Oran Etkin melds traditional West African Malian music with Jewish, Middle Eastern and Jazz rhythms and melodies creating a unique and uplifting sound. Their "hypnotic balance between straight-ahead jazz and world music" (Boston Globe) brings audience to their feet dancing. Thurs., Nov. 10 at 8 p.m. Philadelphia Clef Club of Jazz, 738 South Broad St. Phila. Tickets: $15.00 at www.clefclubofjazz.org or call: 215-893-9912.

For a full listing, of all shows, go to Israeli JazzPhest on Facebook. The Israeli JazzPhest is sponsored by World Café Live, Chris’s Jazz Café, Philadelphia Clef Club of Jazz and Beth Am Israel in partnership with Consulate General of Israel in Philadelphia and made possible in part by the support of the American Israel Cultural Foundation and the Center for Israel and Overseas of the Jewish Federation of Greater Philadelphia.For more information or to set up interviews with the artists, please contact: Deborah Baer Mozes at culture [email protected] or call 215-977-7600, ext. 514....
